TY  - JOUR
T1  - Inventory Service-Level Measures: Convexity and Approximation
AU  - Zipkin, Paul
Y1  - 1986/08/01
PY  - 1986
DA  - 1986/08/01
N1  - doi: 10.1287/mnsc.32.8.975
DO  - 10.1287/mnsc.32.8.975
T2  - Management Science
JF  - Management Science
JO  - Management Science
SP  - 975
EP  - 981
VL  - 32
IS  - 8
PB  - INFORMS
N2  - We argue that standard approximations for two often-used inventory service-level measures may perform poorly in many situations. Then we confirm the long-standing conjecture that the (relatively) exact formulas for these quantities are convex functions of the relevant control variables. Both results suggest the exact expressions should be seriously considered in practical work.
AB  - We argue that standard approximations for two often-used inventory service-level measures may perform poorly in many situations. Then we confirm the long-standing conjecture that the (relatively) exact formulas for these quantities are convex functions of the relevant control variables. Both results suggest the exact expressions should be seriously considered in practical work.
